Definitions:
- Commercial use:
Distribution where the user must pay a fee to access a part or whole of the distributed software, including paying a fee to enable parts of the software, fee to license derivative works of the software, and including compiled binaries generated from the source code if they are distributed.
- Non commercial use:
The entirety of the distributed software is accessible without fee. Optional donation prompts are allowed.
- Software:
Any software licensed under CCL 1.0
- Natural Person:
An individual or group of individuals who do not represent an associated Legal Entity for the purpose of using and/or modifying the Software
- Legal entity:
Any corporation, government entity, nonprofit, company Llc, or similar legal definitions. Natural Persons acting on behalf of a Legal Entity are also considered a Legal entity.

